Dear Instagram

It's real. Is it you too? 

 Your heart  desires to do well by others, to be the best teammate, to give your all? 

And that is good... 

But here is the truth: It can rule us. It can rule me, and once an a while I need to shake off the weight of being everything to everyone. Because the idea that I can-  is a lie. 

 When we have FOLPD we do not serve the God who holds it all. 

When we fear letting others down it is the wrong fuel to our fire. It changes how we use our God given gifting. 

The adjustment is: I will serve God. I will Move when His spirit nudges. I will NOT aim to please man- I will aim to obey God. 

Not easy for this walk-on/ try-hard /work-with-everything-in -me type. 

Especially when I fail.

Which- I don't mind doing on my own. Truly I'm  not afraid to learn something new or even get it wrong trying. There is nothing to lose when I'm the one who has a consequence. I can be bold and unafraid. 

Yet: what takes me down? I'll be really.. real. Feeling like I have let someone down. I hate it. It wrecks me.

Is wanting to do well by others a bad thing? Not always... but check this out :

 that well- intentioned heart,  can become something that condemns me.  As I grow, that lie sneaks in less often - but when it does -it stings. And in need to take the stinger out ! 

God let your children (like me) who desire good, and to do well by others,be propelled ONLY by Your  power, might and instruction and never by the fear of letting someone down. We do not serve earthly masters. We serve YOU alone.

I'm her Bessy. She is my mom ❤️

What it's like to be her daughter. 
Full of awe. 

The day you got me a snoopy sno cone machine that I never thought I would ever receive. 

Watching you continue to lay your life down to serve those around you, to love well, deeply and loyally. 

🤍My mom sure does love well. 

Watching you go to school at night, and watching you walk to receive your law degree. Stamped in my mind forever. 

🤍My mom sure is brilliant 

Witnessing you pray deeply and trusting through your battle with breast cancer. 

🤍My mom battles hard , and  prays+  trusts even harder. 

Watching our children grow up and each day seeing more and  more clearly the gift of sacrificial love - the absolute assurance that the blessing of motherhood is drenched in purpose and is such a privilege. I am a mom running on it my own power or strength. That runs out. I mom on the power of the Holy Spirit within me. And it's within you too. We have a helper. We have our Jesus. 

Today my heart is soaked in gratitude with the gift of being  mom. I get to call my mom and Tim's mom today (who loves me as a daughter) and hug our three right in my arms and that is not taken for granted. To the friend out there that is aching to hold your child or mom- you are not alone. I pray they feel near. I pray the anchored hope of heaven is holding you. I pray peace over your heart today. You are seen. You are loved

Two of my most influential teachers - went to be with Jesus within the same month. 
TIM KELLER 
DR. CHARLES STANLEY
We lived in New York City and would walk with a stroller, then a  double stroller, then a double stroller and a scooter as the kids were growing- to Redeemer where Tim Keller was our pastor. I have countless programs with notes filling the front cover that held the etched "R". Blessed to have learned weekly from Pastor Keller and thankful to have been trusted to write a few lines for this book detailing his life. 

And for  20 years - my ear and heart has grown closer to the Lord thanks to the wisdom of Dr. Charles Stanley. Every morning starts with his devotional in our home. @intouchmin (thank you @donhasselbeckartist @betsyhass 💞) @sandrawstanley @andy_stanley - I have been so led to the Lord again and again and again because of your dad. His conviction and sound judgement made faith personal for me. His mission reached my heart along with millions.

One day I will get to thank them both face to face and face to face with my Savior and Lord. 

🙏🕊️
